# Greeter CLI

A simple command-line tool written in Go to greet users by name.

## âœ¨ Features

- `hello` command to greet someone.
- Optional `--name` flag (or `-n`) to specify the name.
- Defaults to "stranger" if no name is provided.
- Built using the [cobra](https://github.com/spf13/cobra) CLI framework.

---

## ğŸ“¦ Installation

Make sure you have Go installed: [https://go.dev/dl](https://go.dev/dl)

Clone this repo and install dependencies:

```bash
go mod init greeter
go get github.com/spf13/cobra
```

---

## ğŸš€ Usage

Run the CLI:

```bash
go run main.go hello --name Alice
```

Output:

```
Hello, Alice!
```

Without a name:

```bash
go run main.go hello
```

Output:

```
Hello, stranger!
```

---

## ğŸ›  Commands

| Command         | Description               |
|-----------------|---------------------------|
| `hello`         | Say hello to a person     |
| `--name`, `-n`  | Specify the person's name |
| `--help`        | Show help message         |

